#. type: Content of: <sections><section><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:70
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Gentoo Universal LiveCD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:76
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Gentoo Linux can be installed using one of three <e>stage</e> tarball files. A\n"
"stage file is a tarball (compressed archive) that contains a minimal\n"
"environment.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:83
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    A stage1 file contains nothing more than a compiler, Portage (Gentoo's\n"
"    software management system) and a couple of packages on which the \n"
"    compiler or Portage depends. \n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:88
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    A stage2 file contains a so-called bootstrapped system, a minimal\n"
"    environment from which one can start building all other necessary \n"
"    applications that make a Gentoo environment complete.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:93
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    A stage3 file contains a prebuilt minimal system which is almost fully\n"
"    deployable. It only lacks a few applications where you, the Gentoo user, \n"
"    needs to choose which one you want to install.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:100
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We will opt for a stage3 installation throughout this document. If you want to\n"
"perform a Gentoo installation using the stage1 or stage2 files, please use the\n"
"installation instructions in the <uri\n"
"link=\"/doc/en/handbook/handbook-ppc.xml\">Gentoo Handbook</uri>. They do\n"
"require a working Internet connection though.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:110
#, no-wrap
msgid "Gentoo Universal LiveCD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:114
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"A LiveCD is a bootable CDs which contain a self-sustained Gentoo environment. \n"
"It allows you to boot Linux from the CD. During the boot process your hardware \n"
"is detected and the appropriate drivers are loaded. The Gentoo LiveCDs are\n"
"maintained by Gentoo developers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:121
#, no-wrap
msgid "There currently are two LiveCDs available:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:126
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The Universal LiveCD contains everything you need to install Gentoo. It\n"
"    provides stage3 files for common architectures, source code for the extra\n"
"    applications you need to choose from and, of course, the installation\n"
"    instructions for your architecture.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:132
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The Minimal LiveCD contains only a minimal environment that allows you to\n"
"    boot up and configure your network so you can connect to the Internet. It\n"
"    does not contain any additional files and cannot be used during the current\n"
"    installation approach.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:140
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Gentoo also provides a Package CD. This is no LiveCD but an additional resource\n"
"that you can exploit during the installation of your Gentoo system. It contains\n"
"prebuilt packages (the so-called GRP set) that allows you to easily and quickly\n"
"install additional applications (such as OpenOffice.org, KDE, GNOME, ...)\n"
"immediately after the Gentoo installation and right before you update your\n"
"Portage tree.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:149
#, no-wrap
msgid "The use of the Package CD is covered later in this document. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:157
#, no-wrap
msgid "Download, Burn and Boot the Gentoo Universal LiveCD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:159
#, no-wrap
msgid "Downloading and Burning the LiveCD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:163
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can download the Universal LiveCDs (and, if you want to, the Packages CD as\n"
"well) from one of our <uri link=\"/main/en/mirrors.xml\">mirrors</uri>. The\n"
"LiveCDs are located in the <path>releases/ppc/2004.3/livecd</path> directory;\n"
"the Package CDs are located in the <path>releases/ppc/2004.3/packagecd</path>\n"
"directory.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:171
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Inside those directories you'll find so-called ISO-files. Those are full CD \n"
"images which you can write on a CD-R.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:176
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"After downloading the file, you can verify its integrity to see if it is \n"
"corrupted or not:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:182
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    You can check its MD5 checksum and compare it with the MD5 checksum we \n"
"    provide (for instance with the <c>md5sum</c> tool under Linux/Unix or \n"
"    <uri link=\"http://www.etree.org/md5com.html\">md5sum</uri> for Windows)\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:187
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    You can verify the cryptographic signature that we provide. You need to\n"
"    obtain the public key we use (17072058) before you proceed though.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:193
#, no-wrap
msgid "To fetch our public key using the GnuPG application, run the following command:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:196
#, no-wrap
msgid "Obtaining the public key"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:197
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ <i>gpg --keyserver pgp.mit.edu --recv-keys 17072058</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:201
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now verify the signature:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:204
#, no-wrap
msgid "Verify the cryptographic signature"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:205
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ <i>gpg --verify &lt;signature file&gt; &lt;downloaded iso&gt;</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:209
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To burn the downloaded ISO(s), you have to select raw-burning. How you\n"
"do this is highly program-dependent. We will discuss <c>cdrecord</c> and\n"
"<c>K3B</c> here; more information can be found in our <uri\n"
"link=\"/doc/en/faq.xml#isoburning\">Gentoo FAQ</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:217
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    With cdrecord, you simply type <c>cdrecord dev=/dev/hdc &lt;downloaded iso\n"
"    file&gt;</c> (replace <path>/dev/hdc</path> with your CD-RW drive's device\n"
"    path) followed by the path to the ISO file :)\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:222
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    With K3B, select <c>Tools</c> &gt; <c>CD</c> &gt; <c>Burn Image</c>. Then\n"
"    you can locate your ISO file within the 'Image to Burn' area. Finally click\n"
"    <c>Start</c>.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:231
#, no-wrap
msgid "Default: Booting the Universal LiveCD on an Apple/IBM"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:235
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"On NewWorld machines place the LiveCD in the CD-ROM and reboot the system. When\n"
"the system-start-bell sounds, simply hold down the 'C' until the CD loads.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:240
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you have an OldWorld Mac the bootable portion of the livecd can't be used.\n"
"Instead you need to download <uri\n"
"link=\"http://penguinppc.org/projects/bootx/\">BootX</uri> and have a working\n"
"MacOS installed on your system. You need to copy the <c>BootX Extension</c> from\n"
"the unpacked archive-file into the <c>Extensions Folder</c> and make a new\n"
"directory called <c>Linux Kernels</c> in the System Folder. In the next step you\n"
"need to copy the files <c>G3G4kernel</c> and <c>initrd.img.gz</c> from the\n"
"LiveCD <path>boot</path> folder into the <c>Linux Kernels</c> directory. Then\n"
"reboot the system and wait for BootX to load. After BootX loaded you still have\n"
"to set up a few items. In the options dialog you need to check <c>Use Specified\n"
"RAM Disk</c> and select the <c>initrd.img.gz</c> which you put in the <c>Linux\n"
"Kernels</c> directory. The ramdisk size should be set to at least <c>32000</c>.\n"
"Furthermore the kernel argument needs to be set to <c>rw init=/linuxrc\n"
"cdroot</c>.  Eventually you are able to boot the LiveCD when you select Linux on\n"
"Startup.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:258
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"After the LiveCD loaded, you will be greeted by a friendly welcome message and a\n"
"<e>boot:</e> prompt at the bottom of the screen.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:263
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"At this prompt you are able to select a kernel for the subarchitecture you use.\n"
"We provide <c>G3</c>, <c>G4</c> and <c>G5</c>. All kernels are built with\n"
"support for multiple CPUs, but they will boot on single processor machines as\n"
"well.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:270
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You are also able to tweak some kernel options at this prompt. The following\n"
"table lists the available boot options you can add:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><th>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:276
#, no-wrap
msgid "Boot Option"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><th>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:277
#, no-wrap
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:280
#, no-wrap
msgid "<c>video</c>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:282
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    This option takes one of the following vendor-specific tags:\n"
"    <c>radeonfb</c>, <c>rivafb</c>, <c>atyfb</c>, <c>aty128</c> or\n"
"    <c>ofonly</c>. You can follow this tag with the resolution and refreshrate\n"
"    you want to use. For instance <c>video=radeonfb:1280x1024@75</c>. If you are\n"
"    uncertain what to choose, <c>ofonly</c> will most certainly work.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:290
#, no-wrap
msgid "<c>nol3</c>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:292
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Disables level 3 cache on some PowerBooks (needed for at least the 17&quot;)\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:296
#, no-wrap
msgid "<c>debug</c>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:298
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Enables verbose booting, spawns an initrd shell that can be used to debug\n"
"    the LiveCD\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:303
#, no-wrap
msgid "<c>sleep=X</c>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:305
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Wait X seconds before continuing; this can be needed by some very old SCSI\n"
"    CD-ROMs which don't speed up the CD quick enough\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:310
#, no-wrap
msgid "<c>bootfrom=X</c>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:312
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Boot from a different device\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:318
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"At this prompt, hit enter, and a complete Gentoo Linux environment will be\n"
"loaded from the CD. Continue with <uri link=\"#booted\">And When You're\n"
"Booted...</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:326
#, no-wrap
msgid "Alternative: Booting the Universal LiveCD on a Pegasos"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:330
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"On the Pegasos simply insert the CD and at the SmartFirmware boot-prompt type\n"
"<c>boot cd /boot/pegasos</c>. If you need any special boot options you can append them to the\n"
"command-line. For instance <c>boot cd /boot/pegasos video=radeonfb:1280x1024@75 mem=256M</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:338
#, no-wrap
msgid "And When You're Booted..."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:342
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You will be greeted by a root (\"#\") prompt on the current console. You can also \n"
"switch to other consoles by pressing Alt-fn-F2, Alt-fn-F3 and Alt-fn-F4. Get \n"
"back to the one you started on by pressing Alt-fn-F1.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:348
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you are installing Gentoo on a system with a non-US keyboard, use\n"
"<c>loadkeys</c> to load the keymap for your keyboard. To list the available\n"
"keymaps, execute <c>ls /usr/share/keymaps/i386</c>.  Do not use the keymaps in\n"
"<path>ppc</path> or <path>mac</path> as they are for ADB-based OldWorld\n"
"machines.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:355
#, no-wrap
msgid "Listing available keymaps"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:356
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(PPC uses x86 keymaps on most systems. The mac/ppc keymaps provided\n"
" on the LiveCD are ADB keymaps and unusable with the LiveCD kernel)</comment>\n"
"# <i>ls /usr/share/keymaps/i386</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:362
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now load the keymap of your choice:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:365
#, no-wrap
msgid "Loading a keymap"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:366
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>loadkeys be-latin1</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:370
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now continue with <uri link=\"#hardware\">Extra Hardware Configuration</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:376
#, no-wrap
msgid "Extra Hardware Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:380
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When the LiveCD boots, it tries to detect all your hardware devices and\n"
"loads the appropriate kernel modules to support your hardware. In the\n"
"vast majority of cases, it does a very good job. However, in some cases, it may\n"
"not auto-load the kernel modules you need. If the PCI auto-detection missed some\n"
"of your system's hardware, you will have to load the appropriate kernel modules\n"
"manually. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:389
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In the next example we try to load the <c>airport</c> module (support for \n"
"certain kinds of network interfaces):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:393
#, no-wrap
msgid "Loading kernel modules"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:394
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>modprobe airport</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:400
#, no-wrap
msgid "Optional: Tweaking Hard Disk Performance"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:404
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you are an advanced user, you might want to tweak the IDE hard disk\n"
"performance using <c>hdparm</c>. With the <c>-tT</c> options you can\n"
"test the performance of your disk (execute it several times to get a\n"
"more precise impression):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:410
#, no-wrap
msgid "Testing disk performance"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:411
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>hdparm -tT /dev/hda</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:415
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To tweak, you can use any of the following examples (or experiment\n"
"yourself) which use <path>/dev/hda</path> as disk (substitute with your\n"
"disk):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:420
#, no-wrap
msgid "Tweaking hard disk performance"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:421
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>Activate DMA:</comment>                                       # <i>hdparm -d 1 /dev/hda</i>\n"
"<comment>Activate DMA + Safe Performance-enhancing Options:</comment>  # <i>hdparm -d 1 -A 1 -m 16 -u 1 -a 64 /dev/hda</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:428
#, no-wrap
msgid "Optional: User Accounts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:432
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you plan on giving other people access to your installation\n"
"environment or you want to chat using <c>irssi</c> without root privileges (for\n"
"security reasons), you need to create the necessary user accounts and change \n"
"the root password.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:439
#, no-wrap
msgid "To change the root password, use the <c>passwd</c> utility:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:442
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changing the root password"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:443
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>passwd</i>\n"
"New password: <comment>(Enter your new password)</comment>\n"
"Re-enter password: <comment>(Re-enter your password)</comment>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:449
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To create a user account, we first enter their credentials, followed by\n"
"its password. We use <c>useradd</c> and <c>passwd</c> for these tasks.\n"
"In the next example, we create a user called &quot;john&quot;.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:454
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating a user account"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:455
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>useradd -m -G users john</i>\n"
"# <i>passwd john</i>\n"
"New password: <comment>(Enter john's password)</comment>\n"
"Re-enter password: <comment>(Re-enter john's password)</comment>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:462
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can change your user id from root to the newly created user by using\n"
"<c>su</c>:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:466
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changing user id"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:467
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>su - john</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:473
#, no-wrap
msgid "Optional: Viewing Documentation while Installing"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:477
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you want to view the Gentoo Handbook (either from-CD or online) during the\n"
"installation, make sure you have created a user account (see <uri\n"
"link=\"#useraccounts\">Optional: User Accounts</uri>). Then press <c>Alt-F2</c> to\n"
"go to a new terminal and log in.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:484
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you want to view the documentation on the CD you can immediately run\n"
"<c>links2</c> to read it:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:488
#, no-wrap
msgid "Viewing the on-CD documentation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:489
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>links2 /mnt/cdrom/docs/html/index.html</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:493
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"However, it is preferred that you use the online Gentoo Handbook as it will be\n"
"more recent than the one provided on the CD. You can view it using <c>links2</c>\n"
"as well, but only after having completed the <e>Configuring your Network</e>\n"
"chapter (otherwise you won't be able to go on the Internet to view the\n"
"document):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:500
#, no-wrap
msgid "Viewing the Online Documentation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:501
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>links2 http://www.gentoo.org/doc/en/handbook/handbook-ppc.xml</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:505
#, no-wrap
msgid "You can go back to your original terminal by pressing <c>Alt-F1</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:511
#, no-wrap
msgid "Optional: Starting the SSH Daemon"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:515
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you want to allow other users to access your computer during the\n"
"Gentoo installation (perhaps because those users are going to help you\n"
"install Gentoo, or even do it for you), you need to create a user\n"
"account for them and perhaps even provide them with your root password \n"
"(<e>only</e> do that <e>if</e> you <b>fully trust</b> that user).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:523
#, no-wrap
msgid "To fire up the SSH daemon, execute the following command:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:526
#, no-wrap
msgid "Starting the SSH daemon"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:527
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>/etc/init.d/sshd start</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-ppc-medium.xml:531
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To be able to use sshd, you first need to set up your networking. Continue with\n"
"the chapter on <uri link=\"?part=1&amp;chap=3\">Configuring your Network</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""
